                    <h3 class="subheading">A Design That Commands Attention: Style Meets Substance</h3>
                <p>The Yamaha NMax 155 immediately stands out from the crowd of conventional scooters thanks to its quintessential maxi-scooter styling. This design philosophy emphasizes a larger, more imposing, and highly comfortable structure, drawing inspiration from its larger siblings in the international MAX series.</p>
                <p>The front apron is broad and muscular, housing striking twin-LED headlamps that give it an aggressive yet sophisticated face. A tall, blacked-out windscreen further enhances its maxi-scooter appeal and provides excellent wind protection, a major benefit for those longer rides. From the sides, the design is sleek and flowing, with a distinct central spine that adds structural rigidity and aesthetic flair. The overall stance is tall and imposing, yet the riding ergonomics are designed for supreme comfort, making it just as capable on city streets as it is on an open highway. This is a machine built to turn heads, delivering both European flair and Japanese engineering precision.</p>
                <h3 class="subheading">Performance and Engineering: The Heart of the NMax 155</h3>
