                <p>At the core of the <span class="font-weight-700">Yamaha NMax 155</span> is its proven, powerhouse engine—a unit familiar to Indian enthusiasts from the sporty Aerox 155 and R15. This is where the NMax truly separates itself from typical scooters.</p>
                <p>It utilizes a liquid-cooled, 4-stroke, SOHC, 4-valve, 155cc, single-cylinder Blue Core engine. Critically, this engine is equipped with Yamaha’s revolutionary Variable Valve Actuation (VVA) technology. VVA is an advanced feature that optimizes the valve timing for both low-to-mid-range torque and high-end power. This results in a potent combination of brisk acceleration, excellent top-end performance, and surprisingly good fuel efficiency.</p>
                <p>The power is delivered through a smooth V-Belt automatic transmission, ensuring a hassle-free riding experience. While the specific Indian-spec power and torque figures will be confirmed at launch, the international model is known to produce around <span class="font-weight-700">15 PS of power </span>at 8,000 rpm and a peak torque of approximately <span class="font-weight-700">14.4 Nm </span>at 6,000 rpm. This performance pedigree ensures that the NMax 155 is not just a city runabout but a true contender for intercity commutes and highway stretches.</p>
